Project Overview

This project analyzes Python as an open-source software, covering its origin, license, Linux usage, ecosystem, and comparison with proprietary software. It also includes 5 shell scripts demonstrating Linux skills.

Files Included
report.pdf — Project report
script1_system_identity.sh
script2_package_inspector.sh
script3_disk_auditor.sh
script4_log_analyzer.sh
script5_manifesto_generator.sh
Requirements
Linux system
Bash shell
Python3
Basic tools (grep, awk)
How to Run
chmod +x *.sh
./script_name.sh
Scripts Summary
Script 1: System info display
Script 2: Check Python installation
Script 3: Directory size & permissions

🌍 About Python

Created by Guido van Rossum and maintained by Python Software Foundation, Python is widely used in AI, web development, and automation.

📌 Conclusion

This project demonstrates understanding of open-source concepts, Linux environment, and shell scripting.
